NAME: File System Operations Modules
DESCRIPTION: Four modules for creating, deleting, coping and moving files and folders in various FileSystems (VFS)

NAME: Create File System Object Action
DESCRIPTION: This module is used for creating files and folders, names are passed as parameters in configuration. Both input interface and output interface should be NULL interfaces.

NAME: Delete Module
DESCRIPTION: This module is used for deleting files and folders, names are passed as parameters in configuration. Input Interface can be null (in this case file or directory specified by name attribute of module configuration will be deleted, partially or fully dpepending on the folder-itself attribute) or dir. Output Interface should be null.

NAME: Copy Module
DESCRIPTION: This module is used for coping files and folders. First variant is to specify attributes from and to. Second variant is to wrap this module with dir-iterator module and wrap the last one with two dir interfaces. In this case one can choose a set of files to move from some directory by patterns and a special directory where to move files.

NAME: Move Module
DESCRIPTION: This module is used for moving files and folders. First variant is to specify attributes from and to. Second variant is to wrap this module with dir-iterator module and wrap the last one with two dir interfaces. In this case one can choose a set of files to move from some directory by patterns and a special directory where to move files.
